main event: Unidentified aerial objects were photographed at Hondo Air Force Base in Texas on August 27, 1964.
interesting points: The objects appear to have a triangular or pyramidal shape based on the blurry photographs.
The photographs were part of a report from the Foreign Technology Division of the Air Force Systems Command (AFSC).
The report and photographs are marked as 'UNCLASSIFIED'.
There are a total of 10 photographs included in the report, all of which show blurry and indistinct objects in the sky.
The photographs suggest the presence of unidentified aerial phenomena, though the objects are difficult to clearly identify.
sighted object: blurry, indistinct objects with possible triangular or pyramidal shapes
